<LEADPARA>  WE KNOW The Question. It is deceptively simple. And it has dogged us ever
since that first time we got to stay up late and watch from the top of the
stairs as Mom and Dad donned silly hats, blew cardboard horns and indulged in
other mysteriously un-grown-up behavior. Every year, without fail -- somewhere
between the first flying champagne cork of New Year's Eve and the last fizzing
Alka Seltzer of the Tournament of Roses Hangover -- we ask ourselves: "Why do
we do this?";   We do it because after all these years music, dancing,
champagne and people we love are still four of the very best things in life.  </LEADPARA>
