<DESCRIPT>  HOLIDAY; FESTIVAL  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  FIREWORKS, festivals, food and fun are all a part of the long Fourth of July
weekend. Here are some highlights:;    (check) Downtown San Jose: From
Thursday to Sunday, the San Jose America Festival takes over Guadalupe River
Park with a lineup of free performances, a food fair, an arts show and a
children's festival.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  MARK THE FOURTH WITH FESTIVITIES AROUND THE BAY  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  SETTING THE RECORD STRAIGHT (publ. 7/4/91, pg. 2D);  Because of an editor's
error, a Wednesday Living roundup of Fourth of July events incorrectly
described plans at the Harvey West Park in Santa Cruz tonight. There will be
music, food and entertainment, starting at 11 a.m. There will be no fireworks.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     The <ORGANIZATION>America Festival</ORGANIZATION> incorporates five downtown events -- <LOCATION>Kidland</LOCATION>, a
playground/project area for children; the <ORGANIZATION>Great Taste</ORGANIZATION>, a food and music fair;
the Multicultural Arts Showcase; Tapestry in <LOCATION>Talent</LOCATION>, the 16-year-old art fair;
and the Independence Day Fireworks Sky Concert.;    The fireworks will be
launched <DATE>Thursday</DATE> over <LOCATION>Guadalupe River Park</LOCATION> starting between 9:20 and <TIME>9:30
p.m</TIME>. The 20-minute show is choreographed with lights and sound and has its own
score and text. Playwright and director <PERSON>Luis Valdez</PERSON> will deliver the oratory,
and the Fabulous Drifters will start the show with "America the Beautiful.";  
 <ORGANIZATION>The Great Taste</ORGANIZATION>, featuring foods from 20 downtown restaurants, will be open
in <LOCATION>Guadalupe River Park</LOCATION> <TIME>11 a.m. to 9 p.m.</TIME> <DATE>Thursday</DATE> and <TIME>11 a.m.</TIME> to <TIME>7 p.m.</TIME>
<DATE>Friday</DATE>. Kidland, a playground and project area for children, will take over a
section of the park near the <ORGANIZATION>Children's Discovery Museum</ORGANIZATION> from <TIME>11 a.m.</TIME> to <TIME>7
p.m.</TIME> <DATE>Thursday</DATE> and Friday.;    Tapestry in Talent brings artists to <LOCATION>Guadalupe
River Park</LOCATION> and Almaden and Park boulevards from <TIME>10 a.m.</TIME> to <TIME>7 p.m.</TIME> <DATE>Saturday</DATE> and
<DATE>Sunday</DATE>. The entertainment portion of Tapestry in Talent takes place on four
stages both days and features lots of jazz and blues this year.;    Downtown's
newest festival, the Multicultural Arts Showcase, brings to two stages
performing groups from many of the area's ethnic communities <DATE>Thursday</DATE> and
Friday.;    (check) <LOCATION>Great America</LOCATION>: The <LOCATION>Santa Clara</LOCATION> amusement park will be open
<DATE>Thursday</DATE> from <TIME>10 a.m.</TIME> to 11 p.m. <PERSON>Paul Revere</PERSON> and the <ORGANIZATION>Raiders</ORGANIZATION> perform at 4 and
<TIME>8:30 p.m.</TIME>, and the fireworks show begins at <TIME>9:30 p.m.</TIME>;    Many people head for
<LOCATION>Great America</LOCATION> in hopes of finding a spot outside the park to watch the
fireworks for free. Keep in mind that many businesses surrounding <LOCATION>Great
America</LOCATION> reserve their parking lots for their employees on Independence Day.;  
 <LOCATION>Santa Clara City</LOCATION> police plan to divert traffic on streets near <LOCATION>Great America</LOCATION>,
and the <ORGANIZATION>California Highway Patrol</ORGANIZATION> says officers will tow cars that stop along
Highway 101. (408) 988-1776.;    (check) San Jose Giants: The baseball club
features fireworks after the game tonight and <DATE>Thursday</DATE> <TIME>night</TIME>. The games start
at <TIME>7:15 p.m.</TIME> at Municipal Stadium, Tenth and Alma streets, <LOCATION>San Jose</LOCATION>. Admission
is <MONEY>$5</MONEY>, <MONEY>$3</MONEY> for seniors and children. (408) 297-1435.;    (check) <LOCATION>Santa Clara</LOCATION>'s
Fourth of <DATE>July</DATE> Celebration: 17th annual All City Picnic. Pancake breakfast,
entertainment, swimming, games, food booths. Race registration from <TIME>7:15-8:15
a.m.</TIME> Race begins at <TIME>8:30 a.m.</TIME> <DATE>Thursday</DATE>. Ceremony to honor <LOCATION>Santa Clara</LOCATION>'s men
and women in the military services at noon, <LOCATION>Pavilion</LOCATION> picnic area. (408)
984-3257.;    (check) <LOCATION>Sunnyvale Fourth</LOCATION> of <DATE>July</DATE> Celebration: Sponsored by the
<ORGANIZATION>City of Sunnyvale's Parks &amp; Recreation Department</ORGANIZATION>. Pony rides, petting zoo,
